e 2013.</ref>\n* '''Elidio La Torre-Lagares''' (born 1965), poet, novelist, essayist, author of ''Vicios de construcci\u00f3n'' (2008)<ref name=Torres/>\n* '''[[Tato Laviera]]''', poet<br />''Author of \"AmeR\u00edcan\".''<ref>{{Harvnb|Luis|1992|p=1022}}</ref>\n* '''[[Georgina L\u00e1zaro]]''', children's poet<ref name=\"Leon\">[http://www.hitn.tv/noticia_es.php?id=605 ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080307030023/http://www.hitn.tv/noticia_es.php?id=605 |date=7 March 2008 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Muna Lee (writer)|Muna Lee]]''', writer<br /> ''Born in [[Mississippi]], was the first wife of [[Luis Mu\u00f1oz Mar\u00edn]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uhmc.sunysb.edu/surgery/muna.html |title=Muna Lee: A Pan-American Life |publisher=Uhmc.sunysb.edu |date= |accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[Aurora Levins Morales]]''' (born 1954), writer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://voices.cla.umn.edu/artistpages/morales_aurora_levins.php |title=Aurora Levins Morales : Voices From the Gaps : University of Minnesota |publisher=Voices.cla.umn.edu |date= |accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[Jos\u00e9 Liboy Erba (Pepe Liboy)]]''' (born 1964)<ref name=Torres/>\n* '''[[Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Lima]]''' (1934\u20132009), poet, philosopher, mathematician, author of ''La s\u00edlaba en la piel'' (1982)<ref name=Torres/><ref>[[:es:Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Lima]]</ref>\n* '''[[Dahlma Llanos Figueroa]]''' (born 1949), writer, author of ''Daughters of the Stone'', nominated and finalist for the 2010 PEN/America Bingham Award<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dahlmallanosfigueroa.com/ |title=Dahlma Llanos Figueroa Official Website |accessdate=23 October 2019}}</ref>\n* '''[[Luis Llor\u00e9ns Torres]]''', poet<ref name=\"ND\"/>\n* '''[[Washington Llorens]]''', journalist, writer, [[linguistics|linguist]], and scholar<ref name=\"visitponce\"/><ref>[http://www.enciclopediapr1.org/ing/article.cfm?ref=10011901 ]{{dead link|date=March 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[Luis L\u00f3pez Nieves]]''', writer<ref>{